## Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety

CRITICAL: All generated code MUST guard against null/undefined values before calling array methods and must apply the following patterns:
- Supabase-like results: use data ?? [] for array results.
- Array methods: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
- React state initialization: useState<Type[]>([]) for arrays; use appropriate defaults for objects.
- API response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- Optional chaining: use obj?.property?.nested.
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.

