=== EDGE FUNCTIONS & DATABASE MIGRATIONS (MANDATORY) ===

Even without a Supabase project connected, you MUST create the correct files when the task requires them:

EDGE FUNCTIONS - create supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts for:
- LLM/AI features (chat, completions, embeddings, vector search)
- Third-party API integrations (Stripe, SendGrid, Twilio, OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
- Incoming webhooks from external services
- Any server-only logic or logic that must not expose secrets to the client
- Any prompt that says "create edge function" or "add edge function"
File location: supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts
Import pattern: import { serve } from "https://deno.land/std@0.168.0/http/server.ts";
Never expose API keys or secrets in client-side code.

DATABASE MIGRATIONS - create supabase/migrations/<YYYYMMDDHHmmss>_<description>.sql for:
- Every new database table, view, or enum mentioned in the task
- Every schema change (ALTER TABLE, new index, new policy, etc.)
- Any prompt that says "create migration" or describes a data model
Make migrations idempotent (IF NOT EXISTS / CREATE OR REPLACE). Include RLS policies.
Do NOT run "supabase db push" or execute SQL directly — only create the .sql files.

MANDATORY CHECKLIST - Before finishing, verify:
- [ ] Migration SQL file(s) created for every database table/schema change mentioned
- [ ] Edge Function file(s) created for every server-side/secrets feature mentioned
- [ ] TypeScript types created for every new database table

=== TASK ===
# Team Messaging & Notifications

## Overview
Develop a real-time Team Messaging & Notifications subsystem within UnifiedOps that enables: live threaded conversations, user mentions, targeted notification routing (in-app, email, SMS), and digest automation. Provide an integrated experience across Dashboard, Team Messaging Inbox, and Team Messaging Thread pages. Ensure robust runtime safety for all data flows, with explicit guards against null/undefined values before array operations, and proper initialization for React state. Support real-time transport via WebSockets or Server-Sent Events (SSE) with a fallback polling strategy. Include message persistence, search indexing, attachments, mute/pin behavior, unread counts, and token-based authentication/authorization.

---

## Components to Build

1) Real-time Transport Layer (Frontend + Backend)
- Frontend:
  - Establish real-time channel per user or per team room using WebSocket or SSE with automatic reconnect and exponential backoff.
  - Fallback to long-polling when real-time channel is unavailable.
  - Event types: message.new, message.updated, thread.created, thread.archived, user.mentioned, notification.delivered, presence.update.
  - Message composer supports attachments (file uploads with progress), inline previews for images, and mentions (@username) with autocompletion.
- Backend:
  - WebSocket/SSE gateway with per-user channels; scalable approach (use Redis Pub/Sub or a message broker).
  - Message persistence through a messages table; handle delivery guarantees (at-least-once).
  - Presence tracking (online/offline, typing indicator).
  - Rate-limited push for mentions to avoid spam.

2) Message Persistence & Search
- Data models to store messages, threads, channels, attachments, reactions, and read/unread state.
- Full-text search index for messages and threads with support for filtering by user, thread, date, and content.
- Attachments: store metadata (filename, mime-type, size, URL, signed URL exp), and support streaming/downloading.

3) Notifications & Digest Engine
- Notification routing rules:
  - In-app notification per user when they are mentioned, subscribed to a thread, or assigned a task.
  - Email/SMS (Twilio/SendGrid) integration for high-priority or digest delivery per user preferences.
  - Digest automation: daily/weekly digests summarizing unread threads, mentions, and actionable items.
- User preferences: per-channel toggles (in-app, email, SMS), do-not-disturb windows, mute/pin controls, and read receipts.
- Unread counts per thread and global inbox.

4) Inbox (Team Messaging - Inbox)
- UI showing threads list, direct messages, and mentions. Include search, filters (unread, pinned, muted, by user, by channel), and sort (recent activity, unread first).
- Thread overview cards with snippet, last activity timestamp, unread badge, and participant avatars.
- Keyboard shortcuts for compose, search focus, and navigation.

5) Thread View (Team Messaging - Thread)
- Conversation view with:
  - Message history with timestamps, author avatars, and read receipts.
  - Attachments rendering and download/preview.
  - Actions: reply, react, edit (own messages), delete (own messages), pin/unpin, mute thread, mark as unread.
  - Mention parsing with auto-linking to user profiles.
  - Inline reactions and threaded replies (if enabled).
- Attachment uploader with drag-and-drop, progress, and retry logic.
- Real-time updates: new messages append live, message edits reflect instantly, typing indicators.

6) Dashboard (Overview Page)
- KPI panels: unread messages, mentions today, active threads, response SLAs, tasks due.
- Activity feed: a stream of recent messaging events (thread created, message posted, attachments added, mentions).
- Pending tasks integration: show tasks derived from messages or mentions.
- Cashflow snapshot (contextual to notifications, e.g., spending on notifications or action items).
- Quick actions: new thread, new message in a selected thread, mute/unmute thread, set digests.

